    "story_88GJLB": {
      "type": "story",
      "name": "Brand Story",
      "settings": {
        "eyebrow": "— The Brand Story —",
        "heading": "Five quiet chapters.<br><em>One bench.</em>",
        "lede": "Chemistrie was not founded in a boardroom. It was founded one milligram at a time, over a decade, on a single compounding bench in Houston.",
        "chapter_1_year": "2014",
        "chapter_1_heading": "The bench, on Heights Boulevard.",
        "chapter_1_body": "Dr. A and Dr. M meet across the same compounding bench in Houston. A decade of weighing actives by the milligram begins — for patients, for partners, for the women they go home to.",
        "chapter_2_year": "2018",
        "chapter_2_heading": "The first wife. The first formula.",
        "chapter_2_body": "Dr. M's wife asks for a retinol that does not burn. He compounds 0.05% retinaldehyde with niacinamide in a backroom mortar. Within four weeks, six other patients are asking for the same bottle.",
        "chapter_3_year": "2022",
        "chapter_3_heading": "The patient list becomes a waiting list.",
        "chapter_3_body": "Friends of friends. A dermatology nurse's daughter. A schoolteacher in Austin. The bench cannot pour fast enough. The pharmacists begin labelling batches by hand, numbering each bottle as it leaves.",
        "chapter_4_year": "2025",
        "chapter_4_heading": "The maison takes a name.",
        "chapter_4_body": "A glassblower three blocks away. A letterpress in the same city. A photographer who shoots only in west afternoon light. The house is named on a Tuesday — Chemistrie, for the chemistry of patience, hands, and a woman's nightly ritual.",
        "chapter_5_year": "2026",
        "chapter_5_heading": "Today. And the women, still.",
        "chapter_5_body": "Twelve formulas. Two hundred bottles a batch. A pharmacist on the phone, always. Chemistrie is the same bench it always was — only now, with a door open to you."
      }
    },
